arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project has been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-60feef70c6f3481994b63e8b3ac4b91e/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

The project structure:
- `ShipmentTracker/` - server project
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - client/WebAssembly project
- Solution file: `ShipmentTracker.sln`

This is Interactive Auto, Global mode with Individual auth. Key rules:
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Interactive components cannot use DbContext directly — must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, implement with direct DB access on server
- Both Program.cs files register matching services

## Requirements:
1. Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. Authentication is already configured (Individual accounts)

## Implementation Plan:

### 1. Create the Shipment model (shared between projects)

Create a shared models file in the `.Client` project (since both projects can reference it):

File: `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed
}
```

### 2. Create the service interface in the Client project

File: `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync(string email);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Create the HttpClient-based implementation in the Client project

File: `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentServiceClient.cs`
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentServiceClient(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<Shipment?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync(string email)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>($"api/shipments/customer/{Uri.EscapeDataString(email)}") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
    }
}
```

### 4. Create the server-side implementation using EF Core

First, create the DB entity in the server project.

File: `ShipmentTracker/Data/ShipmentEntity.cs`
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ShipmentEntity
{
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [MaxLength(50)]
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public int Status { get; set; }

    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }

    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }

    [MaxLength(256)]
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(500)]
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

Then update `ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add the DbSet. View the current file first to know what to edit.

File: `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServiceServer.cs`
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServiceServer(ApplicationDbContext db) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await db.Shipments.Select(e => MapToModel(e)).ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var entity = await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
        return entity is null ? null : MapToModel(entity);
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync(string email)
    {
        return await db.Shipments
            .Where(s => s.CustomerEmail == email)
            .Select(e => MapToModel(e))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var entity = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (entity is not null)
        {
            entity.Status = (int)status;
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }

    private static Shipment MapToModel(ShipmentEntity e) => new()
    {
        Id = e.Id,
        TrackingNumber = e.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = e.Origin,
        Destination = e.Destination,
        Status = (ShipmentStatus)e.Status,
        ShippedDate = e.ShippedDate,
        EstimatedDelivery = e.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerEmail = e.CustomerEmail,
        Description = e.Description
    };
}
```

### 5. Create API endpoints

File: `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentEndpoints.cs`
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

namespace ShipmentTracker;

public static class ShipmentEndpoints
{
    public static void MapShipmentEndpoints(this WebApplication app)
    {
        var group = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapGet("", async (IShipmentService service) =>
            await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync());

        group.MapGet("track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            var shipment = await service.GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
            return shipment is null ? Results.NotFound() : Results.Ok(shipment);
        });

        group.MapGet("customer/{email}", async (string email, IShipmentService service) =>
            await service.GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync(email));

        group.MapPut("{id}/status", async (int id, ShipmentStatus status, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            await service.UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(id, status);
            return Results.NoContent();
        });
    }
}
```

### 6. Create Pages in the Client project

Remove the template pages (Counter.razor, Weather.razor, Home.razor, Auth.razor) and create:

**Home.razor** - Landing page with track-a-shipment search:
```razor
@page "/"

@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService
@inject NavigationManager Navigation

<PageTitle>ShipmentTracker - Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Track Your Shipment</h1>
<p class="lead">Enter your tracking number to check shipment status and estimated delivery.</p>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="input-group">
            <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter tracking number..."
                   @bind="trackingNumber" @bind:event="oninput"
                   @onkeydown="HandleKeyDown" />
            <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="TrackShipment" disabled="@isLoading">
                @if (isLoading)
                {
                    <span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm me-1"></span>
                }
                Track
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@if (errorMessage is not null)
{
    <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 col-md-6">@errorMessage</div>
}

@if (trackedShipment is not null)
{
    <div class="card mt-4 col-md-8">
        <div class="card-header">
            <strong>Shipment @trackedShipment.TrackingNumber</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="row mb-0">
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Status</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8"><span class="badge bg-@GetStatusColor(trackedShipment.Status)">@trackedShipment.Status</span></dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Origin</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8">@trackedShipment.Origin</dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Destination</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8">@trackedShipment.Destination</dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Description</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8">@trackedShipment.Description</dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Shipped</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8">@trackedShipment.ShippedDate.ToString("MMM dd, yyyy")</dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4">Estimated Delivery</dt>
                <dd class="col-sm-8"><strong>@trackedShipment.EstimatedDelivery.ToString("MMM dd, yyyy")</strong></dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </div>
}

